description:
Benefits:

5 days Work + Bank Holidays
Full Medical Coverage
Sales Incentive
Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave
Training Subsidy
Professional training in digital marketing
Fast track career progression in this growing industry

Responsibilities include:

Identify new clients and perform outbound call selling on our digital marketing consultancy service via phone;
Handle enquiries and provide service information to corporate clients in a professional manner;
Provide support to Business Development Team.

Requirements:

Passionate to digital marketing;
Diploma or above; education background in marketing/ advertising or related discipline will be an advantage;
Possessing at least 1 year of working experience is preferred;
Experience in call center/ B2B customer service is an advantage;
Proficient in both written and oral Chinese and English;
Excellent organizational and communication skills;
High level of customer centric mentality; able to work in a fast-paced environment;
Outstanding candidates will be promoted to Sales Manager after completing on-the-job-training programme.

To Apply:

For more information about You Find Ltd., please visit www.youfind.hk
We offer attractive package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application by clicking "Apply Now".
All information received will be used for recruitment purpose only and will be kept in strict confidential.

YouFind is an Equal Opportunity Employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any kind. All employment decisions at YouFind are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race; family status; gender; disability status or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in Hong Kong.

Responsibilities:

Maximize the sales of our company’s products;
Identify new markets and business opportunities;
Locate and make contact with new and existing customers;
Prepare quotations and negotiate contracts with customers;
Follow up delivery arrangement;
Gather market and customer information;
Handle and review complaints from customers and to set up improvement policy and procedures;

Open up new customers by making cold calls;
Provide after sales services to existing customers;

Requirements:

Form 7 or above.
At least 3 years working experience on sales and marketing works.
Quick thinking and eager to take up responsibility.
Good communication skills and easy to make friends with other people.
Clear mind and able to resolve problems independently.
Able to read and write Chinese.

Salary and Prospect:

Year end bonus will be offered which makes up to totally 14 months salary per year.

After completion of 1 year employment with the performance achieved more than 85% of the works assigned, we will offer at least 10% increase of the second year salary.

Please send your curriculum vitae with expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".

Only short listed candidates will be contacted.  All personal information will be treated with strict confidence for recruitment purpose only, and will be disposed after six months.

- 透過電話向新舊客戶推廣服務產品,
- 透過電話向現存或舊有客人講解最新服務資訊,
- 解答客人的一般查詢 (無需跑數)
- 中五程度; 1年經驗;
- 良好粵語優先; 一般普通話; 一般英語;
- 懂讀寫中文; 略懂讀寫英文;
- 懂視窗操作; 懂MS PowerPoint; 懂MS Excel; 具有一般互聯網知識; 具有基本電腦操作知識; 有電話銷售客戶服務經驗,良好服務態度

To conduct outbound calls to promote HKMC Annuity Plan and marketing campaigns;
To handle customer enquiries or appointment bookings inbound calls in a professional manner;
To work closely with sales and back-office operations team to implement telesales reinforcement initiatives;
To achieve Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) including sales growth and targets as assigned; and
To perform other ad hoc duties and projects as assigned from time to time.
Requirements:
Tertiary educated with a minimum 3 year's sales or customer service experience in the life insurance industry;
Professional telephone manger with strong interpersonal and communication skills, good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua);
Insurance Intermediaries Qualification Papers 1 & 3 is a must;
Sales oriented, responsible and self-motivated; and
Able to work under pressure.
Interested parties please send your full resume starting your current and expected salary by 20 January 2022.
Please visit https://www.hkmca.hk/eng/about_us/careers.html for other application methods.
Please ensure that all information provided to the HKMC Group is accurate, complete and updated. Data provided which is inaccurate or incomplete may influence the process and outcome of the recruitment exercise. Please read the HKMC Group Personal Information Collection Statement for Job Applicants at the HKMCA website before completing the application form. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.

Job Description and Responsibilities:


Handle receptionist's duties of greeting guests, answering phone calls, mailing orders and courier services;
Provide daily administrative support and general clerical duties including filing, data entry;
Present services to customers;
Maintain a positive relationship with clients by providing quality services to customers;

Requirements:

Service-oriented, cheerful and outgoing personality;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills with professional telephone manner;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese, including Mandarin;
Proficiency in MS Office applications such as Word, Excel & Chinese Word processing(倉頡/速成);
Able to work independently with multi-task assignments, attention to details;
Immediate availability is preferred.

Interested candidates please send your resume with date of availability, current and expected salary by clicking “Apply Now”.
